b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av010.htm)  [Next](av012.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 105. Charm against cough.\n\n1\\. As the-soul with the soul's desires swiftly to a distance flies, thus do\nthou, O cough, fly forth along the soul's course of flight!  \n2\\. As a well-sharpened arrow swiftly to a distance flies, thus do thou, O\ncough, fly forth along the expanse of the earth!  \n3\\. As the rays of the sun swiftly to a distance fly, thus do thou, O cough,\nfly forth along the flood of the sea!\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 2. Charm against excessive discharges from the body](av012.htm)\n\n"